CFS Stored Command Table Definitions

CFS Stored Command Configuration Parameters

The following is a list of commands that are processed by the CFS Stored Command Application.

Global SC_APPEND_ATS_CC

Append to an ATS table

Global SC_CONTINUE_ATS_ON_FAILURE_CC

Set the Continue-On-Checksum-Failure flag

Global SC_DISABLE_RTS_CC

DISABLE an RTS

Global SC_DISABLE_RTSGRP_CC

DISABLE a group of RTS

Global SC_ENABLE_RTS_CC

Enable an RTS

Global SC_ENABLE_RTSGRP_CC

ENABLE a group of RTS

Global SC_JUMP_ATS_CC

Jump the time in the running ATS

Global SC_MANAGE_TABLE_CC

Request from cFE Table Services to manage a table

Global SC_NOOP_CC

Noop

Global SC_RESET_COUNTERS_CC

Reset Counters

Global SC_START_ATS_CC

Start an ATS

Global SC_START_RTS_CC

Start an RTS

Global SC_START_RTSGRP_CC

START a group of RTS

Global SC_STOP_ATS_CC

Stop an ATS

Global SC_STOP_RTS_CC

Stop an RTS

Global SC_STOP_RTSGRP_CC

STOP a group of RTS

Global SC_SWITCH_ATS_CC

Switch the running ATS
